25/07/2006
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- EU Commissioner for Environment Stavros Dimas is in Cyprus on Tuesday (25 July), talking with local authorities about improving co-ordination of humanitarian assistance and the evacuation of foreign nationals from Lebanon.
Cyprus has requested the EU's help in dealing with the enormous influx of evacuees, warning that its resources nearly are exhausted.
EU candidate Turkey responded by opening the port of Mersin to new arrivals.
On Monday, Greek President Karolos Papoulias urged the international community to exert every effort to halt the violence between Israel and Lebanon.
(Phileftheros, Kathimerini - 25/07/06;
ANA-MPA, Euronews - 24/07/06)
